div.span: Assertive Advocates are Introverted, Intuitive, Feeling, Judging and Assertive. Advocates are quiet visionaries, often serving as inspiring and tireless idealists. These rare types are open-minded and imaginative, applying care and creativity.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely very imaginative and open-minded, focusing on hidden meanings and distant possibilities.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely decisive, thorough, and highly organized. Values clarity and prefers planning to spontaneity.
Likely self-assured, even-tempered, and resistant to stress, refusing to worry too much.
